---
import {
	adminCommands,
	centerDrops,
	commands,
	guidePages,
	netherDrops,
	netherIslands,
	safetyRules,
	upgrades,
} from "../data/wiki";

const { page } = Astro.props;
const slug = page.slug;
const related = guidePages.filter((item) => item.slug !== slug).slice(0, 3);
---

{
	slug === "getting-started" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>First Steps</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Getting Started</h2>
				</header>
				<div class="section-copy">
					<h3>Your First Island</h3>
					<p>
						When you join, Isles creates your island and sends you there. The
						island starts with grass, dirt, a tree, a protected lodestone core, and a starter chest.
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Starter chest: lava bucket, ice, oak saplings, bone meal, bread, dirt, cobblestone, and string.</li>
						<li>Use <code>/isles island</code> to check your island coordinates.</li>
						<li>Use <code>/setspawn</code> while standing on your island to set your return point.</li>
						<li>Your island core uses lodestone and bedrock protection, so do not plan builds that require removing it.</li>
						<li>The sidebar tracks your PvP zone, island coordinates, Center Shards, generator progress, Center distance, and active events.</li>
						<li>Active islands can receive assisted passive animal spawns and occasional wandering trader checks.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "commands" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Member Commands</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Commands</h2>
				</header>
				<p class="section-copy">
					These are the Isles commands exposed to regular members. Staff-only maintenance commands are intentionally left out.
				</p>
				<div class="table-wrap">
					<table>
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Command</th>
								<th>What It Does</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							{
								commands.map(([command, description]) => (
									<tr>
										<td><code>{command}</code></td>
										<td>{description}</td>
									</tr>
								))
							}
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "staff-tools" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Staff Tools</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Admin Commands</h2>
				</header>
				<div class="section-copy">
					<p>
						These commands require <code>isles.admin</code>, which defaults to operators.
						They control world setup, Center events, dimension unlocks, migration, and reset workflows.
					</p>
				</div>
				<div class="table-wrap">
					<table>
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Command</th>
								<th>What It Does</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							{
								adminCommands.map(([command, description]) => (
									<tr>
										<td><code>{command}</code></td>
										<td>{description}</td>
									</tr>
								))
							}
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
				<div class="note-row">
					<p>New installs auto-register the Center generator for the overworld and void generators for the Nether and End.</p>
					<p>After updating from legacy MSB, use <code>/isles migrate</code> to smart-merge old config/data and retag online Center Shards.</p>
					<p>Existing terrain may still need <code>/isles worldreset confirm</code> or a manual world reset to become true void terrain.</p>
					<p>World reset requests are queued with a flag file and are processed on the next server startup before Paper loads the worlds.</p>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "teams" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Shared Islands</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Teams</h2>
				</header>
				<p class="section-copy">
					Teams let several players share one island. The leader owns the shared island, manages invites,
					and controls team-only actions such as renaming or kicking.
				</p>
				<div class="steps">
					<div>
						<span>1</span>
						<h3>Create</h3>
						<p>Use <code>/team create &lt;name&gt;</code>. Names can use letters, numbers, spaces, or hyphens, and must be 3-24 characters.</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<span>2</span>
						<h3>Invite</h3>
						<p>Team leaders can use <code>/team invite &lt;player&gt;</code>. The player must be online and not already on a team.</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<span>3</span>
						<h3>Accept</h3>
						<p>Accepting joins the leader's island. The accepting player's old solo island is wiped.</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<span>4</span>
						<h3>Leave</h3>
						<p>Members who leave or get kicked receive a fresh island. If a leader leaves or disbands a multi-player team, leadership transfers and the old leader receives a fresh island.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "upgrades" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Generator Upgrades</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Generator Menu</h2>
				</header>
				<p class="section-copy">
					Open <code>/isles upgrades</code> to spend Center Shards and materials. Generator upgrades affect
					cobblestone or stone that forms from your generator.
				</p>
				<div class="upgrade-grid">
					{
						upgrades.map((upgrade) => (
							<section>
								<div>
									<h3>{upgrade.name}</h3>
									<code>/isles upgrades buy {upgrade.buy}</code>
								</div>
								<p>{upgrade.effect}</p>
								<dl>
									<div>
										<dt>Cost</dt>
										<dd>{upgrade.cost}</dd>
									</div>
									<div>
										<dt>Note</dt>
										<dd>{upgrade.note}</dd>
									</div>
								</dl>
							</section>
						))
					}
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "center" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>The Center</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Asteroid Field</h2>
				</header>
				<div class="split">
					<div>
						<p>
							The center is the asteroid field around world spawn. It is the main place to earn
							Center Shards, mine renewable resource nodes, find crates, and fight other players.
						</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Center radius: about 160 blocks from 0,0 by default.</li>
							<li>PvP is enabled inside the center.</li>
							<li>Regular resource nodes respawn after about 15 minutes.</li>
							<li>Center events last 20 minutes and add bonus nodes plus event crates.</li>
							<li>The asteroid field includes rocky, metallic, crystal, volcanic, icy, and ruined archetypes with generated structures and crates.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="stat-card">
						<h3>Event Loot</h3>
						<p>
							Events add 12 bonus nodes and 5 crates. Event crates can include 4-7 Center Shards
							plus items like diamonds, golden apples, XP bottles, ender pearls, and amethyst shards.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="table-wrap compact">
					<table>
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Vein</th>
								<th>Drop</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							{
								centerDrops.map(([node, drop]) => (
									<tr>
										<td>{node}</td>
										<td>{drop}</td>
									</tr>
								))
							}
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "nether" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Nether Archipelago</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Custom Nether</h2>
				</header>
				<p class="section-copy">
					The Nether is locked until staff unlocks it for the SMP. Once unlocked, Nether portals
					send you to the managed archipelago hub instead of normal Nether terrain. Returning from
					the managed Nether sends you back to your island spawn.
				</p>
				<div class="list-grid">
					{
						netherIslands.map(([name, description]) => (
							<section>
								<h3>{name}</h3>
								<p>{description}</p>
							</section>
						))
					}
				</div>
				<div class="note-row">
					<p>Nether resource nodes respawn after about 20 minutes.</p>
					<p>Ancient debris nodes respawn after about 2 hours, with up to 4 active at once by default.</p>
					<p>Bastion hotspots are PvP zones and double most Nether node drops. Ancient debris still drops one scrap.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="table-wrap compact">
					<table>
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Node</th>
								<th>Drop</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							{
								netherDrops.map(([node, drop]) => (
									<tr>
										<td>{node}</td>
										<td>{drop}</td>
									</tr>
								))
							}
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "end" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>The End</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Shared Dragon Arena</h2>
				</header>
				<div class="section-copy">
					<p>
						The End is locked until staff unlocks it. When it opens, a shared End portal appears
						at the center above the asteroid field. Everyone uses the same void arena and dragon fight.
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>The entry platform is obsidian near the arena edge.</li>
						<li>The arena is a round End Stone island at Y 64 with obsidian pillars and crystals.</li>
						<li>The dragon stays active and targets nearby survival or adventure players within about 160 blocks.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "safety" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Safety And Rules</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Player Safety</h2>
				</header>
				<ul class="rule-list">
					{safetyRules.map((rule) => <li>{rule}</li>)}
				</ul>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

<section class="band">
	<h2>Related Pages</h2>
</section>

<section class="browse-grid" aria-label="Related wiki pages">
	{
		related.map((item) => (
			<a class="browse-card search-card" href={`/${item.slug}/`} data-search={`${item.title} ${item.text} ${item.search}`}>
				<img class="mc-icon" src={item.icon} alt="" />
				<strong>{item.title}</strong>
				<small>{item.text}</small>
			</a>
		))
	}
</section>
